<p>I have a question following the previous one asked <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/24783704/how-to-do-active-directory-authentication-in-razor-cshtml?newreg=c209927c5f4e4939ac67c400a415040c" title="here">here</a>. </p>  <p>Using the same principle as the mentioned in the answer how can I perform authentication for a secure online system with below requirements? </p>  <p><strong>System Requirements</strong></p>  <ul> <li>Use Razor/cshtml as a core development technology</li> <li>Provide authentication to site using AD </li> <li>Host AD within the same infrastructure as the IIS host </li> <li>Expanding on the previous one - enabling access to site features using AD groups</li> <li>Be accessible over internet link which is publicly viewable</li> <li>Provide best security possible to the data stored within the system </li> </ul>  <p><strong><em>Note:</em></strong> Please feel free to add any sound security concerns that may arise from combining the above requirements. </p>